The Kentucky Diabetes Research Board is created for the purpose of administering the diabetes research trust fund. The board shall be composed of the secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or the secretary's designee and seven (7) members appointed by the Governor as follows:
Two (2) members representing the University of Kentucky College of Medicine;
Two (2) members representing the University of Louisville School of Medicine;
One (1) member who has diabetes or who has a family member with diabetes;
One (1) member who is a physician with experience with research or treatment of diabetes; and
One (1) at-large member who has a health care policy perspective on diabetes issues as a patient, health care provider, consultant, or in business.
